name: zipfile-deflate64
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "zipfile-deflate64" %}
{% set version = "0.2.0" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 875a3299de102edf1c17f8cafcc528b1ca80b62dc4814b9cb56867ec59fbfd18

build:
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 2
  skip: true  # [py2k]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - zipfile_deflate64
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/brianhelba/zipfile-deflate64
  summary: Extract Deflate64 ZIP archives with Python's zipfile API.
  dev_url: https://github.com/brianhelba/zipfile-deflate64
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - sarthakpati
